question.title: My Junit test file has Unknown module: warnings
question.body:
I'm using Java SE-21 and JUnit 5 in Eclipse JEE, and I'm trying to test a StringTest class as a JUnit Test.

The test file is:

package com.in28minutes.junit5;

import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;

import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;

class StringTest {
    @Test
    void test() {
        fail("Not yet implemented");
    }
}

I expected the code to run with no errors and one failure. The result was the code didn't run through the test due to some configuration issue. I got these three warnings on setup instead:

WARNING: Unknown module: junit5 specified to --patch-module
WARNING: Unknown module: junit5 specified to --add-reads
WARNING: Unknown module: junit5 specified to --add-opens

Here's a screenshot of the project set-up.

How can I test my class properly?
